very accurately weighing the

00:10:35.300 --> 00:10:40.070
elements. He has arranged the
elements here in a column.

00:10:40.070 --> 00:10:44.840
It is a double column, but it is
only made double for convenience.

00:10:44.840 --> 00:10:49.610
You can see, it starts with
hydrogen and goes to mercury in

00:10:49.610 --> 00:10:53.750
ascending order of atomic mass.
And he was very proficient at

00:10:53.750 --> 00:10:57.250
measuring atomic mass.
And, furthermore, he started to

00:10:57.250 --> 00:11:00.750
abbreviate. Instead of writing gold
he made this symbol.

00:11:00.750 --> 00:11:04.250
Silver was S with a circle.
He could have worked on a ranch out

00:11:04.250 --> 00:11:07.750
in the West, couldn't he?
This looks like branding things,

00:11:07.750 --> 00:11:11.250
don't they? Well, this is
interesting, cute fonts,

00:11:11.250 --> 00:11:14.750
but in point of fact they were
short-lived. Berzelius,

00:11:14.750 --> 00:11:18.250
the Swedish chemist suggested that
the French might take umbrage at

00:11:18.250 --> 00:11:21.770
having to use I for iron.
He said why don't we choose

00:11:21.770 --> 00:11:25.330
something neutral?
Let's choose Latin,

00:11:25.330 --> 00:11:28.880
the language of scholarship,
and so iron became Fe for ferrum and

00:11:28.880 --> 00:11:32.440
lead became Pb for plumbum and gold
is Au for aurum and so on.

00:11:32.440 --> 00:11:35.990
And nobody quibbles because nobody
speaks Latin so it is neutral for

00:11:35.990 --> 00:11:39.550
everybody. John Dalton also talked
about other things.

