it is sometimes frustrating. But I
will use various forms.

00:21:47.660 --> 00:21:54.280
Mendeleev wrote the following.
He says that the properties of the

00:21:54.280 --> 00:22:02.850
elements are, or let's say vary,
the properties of the elements vary

00:22:02.850 --> 00:22:11.420
periodically with atomic mass.
We will find out later that is

00:22:11.420 --> 00:22:26.173
almost correct.
There is a slight variant on there.

00:22:00.000 --> 00:22:23.520
But right now I am going to give it
to you as Mendeleev enunciated it.

00:22:23.520 --> 00:22:27.050
Atomic number, we will learn later,
is the improvement. That is why

00:22:27.050 --> 00:22:30.580
this says atomic number,
but for most intents and purposes we

00:22:30.580 --> 00:22:34.110
can say this could be atomic mass.
What I am looking at here is

00:22:34.110 --> 00:22:37.640
boiling point as a function of
atomic number.

00:22:37.640 --> 00:22:41.170
And what we see is it is not
monotonic. It is not continuously

00:22:41.170 --> 00:22:44.700
rising, continuously falling.
It seems to rise and then fall.

00:22:44.700 --> 00:22:48.230
And then it rises and then it falls.
And then it rises

00:22:48.230 --> 00:22:52.060
and then it falls.
And it rises and then it falls.

00:22:52.060 --> 00:22:56.180
And, if you laid this out in a
table, as Mendeleev did with his

00:22:56.180 --> 00:23:00.310
cards, you would find that the local
maxima all occur roughly in the same

00:23:00.310 --> 00:23:04.430
horizontal position from the end
points of the rows.

00:23:04.430 --> 00:23:08.550
And then there is a trend going
from least massive to most massive.

00:23:08.550 --> 00:23:12.680
So that is where the "periodic"
comes from. We have a table of the

00:23:12.680 --> 00:23:16.810
elements with properties varying
periodically with atomic mass,

00:23:16.810 --> 00:23:20.930
so we compress all of that
information and refer to it

00:23:20.930 --> 00:23:24.710
as the Periodic Table.
Here is atomic radius versus atomic

00:23:24.710 --> 00:23:28.140
number. You see the radius is high
and then it falls.

00:23:28.140 --> 00:23:31.570
It rises, it falls.
It rises, it falls. It rises,

00:23:31.570 --> 00:23:34.990
it falls. We are going to now go
into the atom and try to understand

00:23:34.990 --> 00:23:38.420
the scientific basis for this
observed behavior.

00:23:38.420 --> 00:23:41.850
And so here is the Periodic Table
in its glory today following on

00:23:41.850 --> 00:23:45.280
Mendeleev's scheme.
The elements have been named up

00:23:45.280 --> 00:23:49.530
through --
The one that you are getting hasn't

00:23:49.530 --> 00:23:54.610
got the latest information.
This was named over the past summer.

00:23:54.610 --> 00:23:59.690
This is element 110 which has been
named darmstadtium after Darmstadt.

00:23:59.690 --> 00:24:04.760
And I will tell you why in a minute.
If you do look down at the Periodic

00:24:04.760 --> 00:24:09.840
Table and get above 109,
you will see these strange notations

00:24:09.840 --> 00:24:14.920
here, Uun, Uuu,
Uub. What is all of this?

00:24:14.920 --> 00:24:32.973
These are elements that have yet to
be isolated.

00:24:00.000 --> 00:24:10.000
These are elements that are unstable.
These are what are known as the

00:24:10.000 --> 00:24:20.000
superheavies. Elements beyond
uranium, these are synthetic.

00:24:20.000 --> 00:24:30.000
And where are they made? The
manufacturing facility.

00:24:30.000 --> 00:24:55.270
There are three places on the planet
that have the high energy physics

00:24:55.270 --> 00:25:00.540
equipment in order to make these,
and these are the three places. One

00:25:00.540 --> 00:25:05.810
is Dubna in the former Soviet Union
in Russia, one is in Darmstadt in

00:25:05.810 --> 00:25:11.080
Germany and the third one is in the
United States in Berkeley.

00:25:11.080 --> 00:25:16.360
These are the three places where
they have the accelerators.

00:25:16.360 --> 00:25:21.380
And the kinds of reactions --
Here is how they were able to make

00:25:21.380 --> 00:25:26.150
darmstadtium. They take an atom of
lead, accelerate it and have it

00:25:26.150 --> 00:25:30.920
collide with an atom of nickel.
And, if the conditions are right,

00:25:30.920 --> 00:25:35.690
they will combine, fuse and form
darmstadtium plus neutron.

00:25:35.690 --> 00:25:40.460
So these devices, when I was a
youngster, were colloquially known

00:25:40.460 --> 00:25:45.230
as "atom smashers",
because they have the capacity to

00:25:45.230 --> 00:26:03.193
actually break these and
have them reform.

00:25:30.000 --> 00:25:53.750
And there are various forces that
play in the nucleus that will

00:25:53.750 --> 00:26:13.533
dictate when this will be stable and
when it won't be.

00:25:37.500 --> 00:26:01.250
They isolated it,
but it decays very quickly on the

00:26:01.250 --> 00:26:20.566
order of microseconds.
Lifetime on the order of

00:25:45.000 --> 00:26:08.750
microseconds. So,
you can imagine, that is why we

00:26:08.750 --> 00:26:29.133
don't have the boiling point of
darmstadtium and its electrical

00:25:52.500 --> 00:26:16.250
conductivity. They have isolated it
enough that they can actually say

00:26:16.250 --> 00:26:35.166
the bare minimum about
it. So we have it.

00:26:00.000 --> 00:26:24.610
And then, just so that you will be
literate in the rest of the Periodic

00:26:24.610 --> 00:26:29.220
Table, if you look at the higher
ones, this is how you name them.

00:26:29.220 --> 00:26:33.840
Use these Latin prefixes. 111
would be un plus un plus un.

00:26:33.840 --> 00:26:38.460
So 115 is ununpentium. That is why
you see these Uup,

00:26:38.460 --> 00:26:43.070
Uun. My favorite is 111 because
that is unununium.

00:26:43.070 --> 00:26:47.690
I am going to be sad when they
finally get a name for

00:26:47.690 --> 00:26:52.140
it. There they are.
And, when they are named,

00:26:52.140 --> 00:26:56.420
they are named by suggestion by the
scientist who have isolated them.

00:26:56.420 --> 00:27:00.710
And there is a lot of competition.
Obviously, if it is Russian team

00:27:00.710 --> 00:27:04.990
that isolates the element,
they are going to advocate the name

00:27:04.990 --> 00:27:09.280
of a Russian scientist or a Russian
location or whatnot.

00:27:09.280 --> 00:27:13.570
Obviously, the work that was done
to isolate 110 was done in Germany

00:27:13.570 --> 00:27:17.850
and they proposed the name Darmstadt.
And, hence, it is named

00:27:17.850 --> 00:27:21.940
darmstadtium.
There is a dubnium and there is also

00:27:21.940 --> 00:27:25.820
a berkelium. And,
if you look in the very high numbers,

00:27:25.820 --> 00:27:29.700
you will see these nomenclatures.
There is darmstadtium sitting there.

