00:27:57.150 --> 00:28:01.300
After you have had these lectures,
it will be a joy to read. Now let's

00:28:01.300 --> 00:28:05.460
go inside the atom to try to
understand what is going on.

00:28:05.460 --> 00:28:09.610
And this is taken from your book,
Table 1.3. And so these are the

00:28:09.610 --> 00:28:13.760
subatomic particles that we have to
contend with. We have the electron.

00:28:13.760 --> 00:28:17.920
It bears a negative charge and the
value of minus 1.6 times

00:28:17.920 --> 00:28:36.640
10 to the 19 coulombs.
This is the SI unit,

00:28:02.000 --> 00:28:06.000
the systeme international unit for
electric charge.

00:28:06.000 --> 00:28:10.000
And it has a mass of 9.
1 times 10 to the minus 31 kilograms.

00:28:10.000 --> 00:28:14.000
The charge compensation comes out
of the nucleus with the proton and

00:28:14.000 --> 00:28:18.000
it is positive 1.
times 10 to the minus 19 coulombs.

00:28:18.000 --> 00:28:22.000
But its mass is 1800 times that of
the electron. The electron is just

00:28:22.000 --> 00:28:26.000
a little gnat in comparison to the
proton. And then there is this

00:28:26.000 --> 00:28:30.000
third species, the neutron,
which has no charge.

00:28:30.000 --> 00:28:36.000
Roughly equal in mass to that of the
proton. And so what we do,

00:28:36.000 --> 00:28:42.000
in order to designate the identity
of an atom, is the following.

00:28:42.000 --> 00:28:48.000
This is the atomic symbol which was
given by Berzelius.

00:28:48.000 --> 00:28:54.000
This is the Latin one or two letter
character. And we began with the

00:28:54.000 --> 00:29:00.000
proton number.
The proton number is in the lower

00:29:00.000 --> 00:29:26.250
left corner. Z proton number.
Number of protons in the nucleus,

00:29:26.250 --> 00:29:32.750
this is number of protons in the
nucleus, which in the neutral atom

00:29:32.750 --> 00:29:47.900
is equal to the number of electrons.

00:29:20.000 --> 00:29:25.000
Now, to get to the number of
neutrons, what we do is go up here

00:29:25.000 --> 00:29:30.000
to the upper left.
And this is called the atomic mass.

00:29:30.000 --> 00:29:54.280
And it is equal to the sum of the
number of protons plus the number of

00:29:54.280 --> 00:29:58.560
neutrons. So we get at the number
of neutrons indirectly because we

00:29:58.560 --> 00:30:02.850
know the proton number here.
This is sum of protons plus

00:30:02.850 --> 00:30:07.140
neutrons. And we don't put the mass
of the electrons because they are so

00:30:07.140 --> 00:30:11.420
light in comparison.
This will give us the sum that we

00:30:11.420 --> 00:30:15.710
need. And, at some level,
there is some redundancy here.

00:30:15.710 --> 00:30:35.020
If we want to write sodium, for
example, sodium 23, 11.

00:30:00.000 --> 00:30:25.090
Well, 11 means it is sodium.
If you have 11 protons, it must be

00:30:25.090 --> 00:30:30.180
sodium. We could get away with just
23 Sodium **23Na**,

00:30:30.180 --> 00:30:35.270
but if you wanted to be a real
smart-aleck you could write sodium

00:30:35.270 --> 00:30:40.360
like this. You don't need anything
here. Just a suggestion.

00:30:40.360 --> 00:30:45.450
Now, atoms need not be neutral.
They can be charge deficient or

00:30:45.450 --> 00:30:51.750
charge excessive.
And so Michael Faraday coined the

00:30:51.750 --> 00:30:59.250
term "ion" for atoms of net charge,
atoms and other species bearing net

00:30:59.250 --> 00:31:11.500
charge.

00:30:48.000 --> 00:31:14.400
For example, the positive ions,
these are electron deficient. We

00:31:14.400 --> 00:31:20.790
cannot do anything about protons,
they are buried in the nucleus, but

00:31:20.790 --> 00:31:26.790
we can add or subtract electrons.
The positive ions are electron

00:31:26.790 --> 00:31:32.390
deficient, and these are known as
cations. And you can use mnemonics

00:31:32.390 --> 00:31:37.990
to try to keep these straight.
I see the T as sort of a plus sign.

00:31:37.990 --> 00:31:43.590
It comes from the fact that in an
electrochemical cell,

00:31:43.590 --> 00:31:49.190
the cations are those that are
reduced. You know from catastrophe,

00:31:49.190 --> 00:31:54.540
cata is Greek for down.
Catastrophe is a downturn.

00:31:54.540 --> 00:31:59.630
So that is the cation. The
negative ions,

00:31:59.630 --> 00:32:04.720
these are electron-rich.
They have an excess of electrons.

00:32:04.720 --> 00:32:09.810
And these are known as anions. It
has the n, which might conjure up

00:32:09.810 --> 00:32:14.900
negative, or anion and minus both
have five letters.

00:32:14.900 --> 00:32:34.266
I don't know how you want to try to
keep those straight, but anyway.

00:32:00.000 --> 00:32:25.590
Those mnemonics sometimes come in
handy. All right.

00:32:25.590 --> 00:32:31.190
Now the last thing is that because
the neutron has no net charge,

00:32:31.190 --> 00:32:36.790
we can change neutron number.
Neutron has no charge.

00:32:36.790 --> 00:32:42.390
This means you can vary the neutron
number without changing chemical

00:32:42.390 --> 00:33:00.646
identity, because chemical identity
is fixed by the proton.

00:32:28.000 --> 00:32:53.450
And since we don't have to charge
compensate, we can add or subtract

00:32:53.450 --> 00:32:58.900
neutrons at liberty.
And so you can look,

00:32:58.900 --> 00:33:04.360
for example, at the Periodic Table.
And, if you look up the atomic mass

00:33:04.360 --> 00:33:09.810
of carbon, you will see that carbon
comes at 12.011 for carbon.

00:33:09.810 --> 00:33:15.270
Well, isn't this against Dalton?
This thing is supposed to be a

00:33:15.270 --> 00:33:33.873
whole number here.
But, if you look more carefully,

00:33:00.000 --> 00:33:04.000
you will find that this is a blend
of three different forms of carbon.

00:33:04.000 --> 00:33:08.000
We have carbon 12. I will even
leave off the 6 because we already

00:33:08.000 --> 00:33:12.000
know it is carbon.
It has to have 6 protons.

00:33:12.000 --> 00:33:16.000
So carbon 12. We know that it has
the proton number,

00:33:16.000 --> 00:33:20.000
by definition, is 6.
And the neutron number,

00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:24.000
6 from 12 is 6. So it has 6 protons
and 6 neutrons.

00:33:24.000 --> 00:33:28.000
And it is the dominant form of
carbon.

00:33:28.000 --> 00:33:53.810
So its abundance in nature is 98.
92%. There is a carbon 13, however.

00:33:53.810 --> 00:33:59.630
It axiomatically must be 6 protons,
and it has 7 neutrons.

00:33:59.630 --> 00:34:05.450
And this found in an abundance of
about 1.108%. And then there are

00:34:05.450 --> 00:34:11.270
the last four,
carbon 14, which is a radioactive

00:34:11.270 --> 00:34:17.090
form. And we will talk about that
later in 3.091.

00:34:17.090 --> 00:34:23.090
And its use in radiocarbon dating.
And carbon 14,

00:34:23.090 --> 00:34:29.270
6 again and it has 8,
and it is found in vanishingly small

00:34:29.270 --> 00:34:35.450
amounts, 10 to the minus 12 or part
per trillion. If you add all these

00:34:35.450 --> 00:34:41.630
up then you end up with 12.
11 as the atomic mass. They all

00:34:41.630 --> 00:34:47.810
have the same Z,
the same proton number,

00:34:47.810 --> 00:35:05.220
but different A, which means number
of neutrons varies.

00:34:34.000 --> 00:34:59.190
That means they are found on the
same place on the Periodic Table.

00:34:59.190 --> 00:35:04.390
If they are found on the same place,
it is iso-topos.

00:35:04.390 --> 00:35:09.590
These are called isotopes.
Isotopes have the same chemical

00:35:09.590 --> 00:35:14.790
identity but different nuclear
properties. What are the units here?

00:35:14.790 --> 00:35:32.513
We write 12.011. It is
either grams per mole.

00:35:00.000 --> 00:35:26.660
And I am not making a mistake here.
Most of chemistry has gone SI so

00:35:26.660 --> 00:35:33.330
every mass should be in kilograms.
But occasionally there is this one

00:35:33.330 --> 00:35:39.990
little remnant of the old CGS system,
centimeters-gram-second,

00:35:39.990 --> 00:35:46.660
and this is one. This is 12.
11 grams per mole or 12.011 atomic

00:35:46.660 --> 00:35:54.280
mass units, AMU.
And the AMU is defined as the mass

00:35:54.280 --> 00:36:02.850
of one-twelfth of a carbon 12 atom.
I talked about this concept of mole

00:36:02.850 --> 00:36:11.420
here. What is the mole?
Mole is a more practical value,

00:36:11.420 --> 00:36:25.306
something that we can handle
tangibly.

00:36:00.000 --> 00:36:28.570
And how do we get the value of the
mole? The mole is something that

00:36:28.570 --> 00:36:37.140
was also defined in terms of carbon.
And the mole is defined as the mass

00:36:37.140 --> 00:36:45.710
of, excuse me.
It is the amount of carbon 12

00:36:45.710 --> 00:36:52.580
weighing exactly 12.000 grams.
You can see the atomic mass unit

00:36:52.580 --> 00:36:57.740
will be, excuse me.
Let me go at it a different way.

00:36:57.740 --> 00:37:02.910
This will be the definition of the
mole as the amount of carbon

00:37:02.910 --> 00:37:08.080
weighing exactly 12 grams,
so I would like to know now how many

00:37:08.080 --> 00:37:13.240
particles, how many carbons are
there in that mole.

00:37:13.240 --> 00:37:18.410
And one way we can get to that is
by looking at two pieces of data.

00:37:18.410 --> 00:37:24.220
The first one, again, is by Faraday.
Faraday conducted electrolysis of

00:37:24.220 --> 00:37:30.660
silver. In an aqueous solution,
he passes electric current and

00:37:30.660 --> 00:37:37.110
causes silver ions to deposit and
form metallic silver.

00:37:37.110 --> 00:37:43.550
And he measures how much charge is
required. He has current.

00:37:43.550 --> 00:38:01.766
We know that charge is equal to the
integral of current times the time.

00:37:30.000 --> 00:37:35.000
And he knows the current,
he knows how much time and then he

00:37:35.000 --> 00:37:40.000
weighs this. So he is able to
weighthe silver and compare it to

00:37:40.000 --> 00:37:45.000
carbon. And, against that scale,
he finds the silver weighs 107 grams

00:37:45.000 --> 00:37:50.000
versus 12 grams for carbon.
That is the ratio. Now, if he only

00:37:50.000 --> 00:37:55.000
knew what the electron brought him
he would be able to divide through

00:37:55.000 --> 00:38:00.000
and calculate how many species there
are in a mole.

00:38:00.000 --> 00:38:06.000
And, in order to determine that,
we had to wait a few years until

00:38:06.000 --> 00:38:12.000
1909. In 1909 Robert Millikan doing
experiments at the University of

00:38:12.000 --> 00:38:18.000
Chicago conducted this interesting
effort where he took atomizer,

00:38:18.000 --> 00:38:24.000
filled it with oil and then squirted
fine droplets of oil mist in between

00:38:24.000 --> 00:38:30.000
two plates that could be
electrically charged.

00:38:30.000 --> 00:38:54.900
He further charged the droplets by
irradiating. Here it is showing

00:38:54.900 --> 00:38:59.810
x-rays. He used x-rays.
He used various forms of

00:38:59.810 --> 00:39:04.720
high-energy radiation in order to
make the droplets bear a charge.

00:39:04.720 --> 00:39:09.630
Now you have this situation where
you have a droplet that is net

00:39:09.630 --> 00:39:14.540
negative or perhaps net positive.
And it lies suspended between two

00:39:14.540 --> 00:39:19.190
plates.
And I am able to vary the voltage on

00:39:19.190 --> 00:39:23.590
the plates making this for
argument's sake negative and this

00:39:23.590 --> 00:39:27.990
for argument's sake positive.
If there is no charge on the plate,

00:39:27.990 --> 00:39:32.390
these droplets will simply fall
under gravity.

00:39:32.390 --> 00:39:36.790
Once the droplets are charged it
makes no difference.

00:39:36.790 --> 00:39:41.190
They will fall regardless of the
charge. When the charge is applied,

00:39:41.190 --> 00:39:45.590
if the upper plate is negative, we
would expect that the negative

00:39:45.590 --> 00:40:05.713
droplet would be repelled at a rate
exceeding the gravitational fall.

00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:54.830
The positive droplet,
its fall will be slowed and could

00:39:54.830 --> 00:39:59.660
even be made to lift.
And so, by playing with a variety

00:39:59.660 --> 00:40:04.490
of sizes, remember the atomizer is
going to give a distribution of

00:40:04.490 --> 00:40:09.330
droplet sizes,
a distribution of voltages,

00:40:09.330 --> 00:40:14.160
Millikan was able to develop a
relationship between the applied

00:40:14.160 --> 00:40:32.653
charge and the observed velocities
of the droplets.

00:39:59.000 --> 00:40:24.160
Let's plot droplet velocity as a
function of looking at the number

00:40:24.160 --> 00:40:29.330
that have this velocity with the
zero being in the center here.

00:40:29.330 --> 00:40:34.490
What do you expect is going to
happen? If there were no voltage on

00:40:34.490 --> 00:40:39.660
the plates, we would expect
everything to be over here in some

00:40:39.660 --> 00:40:44.830
negative value falling.
But what he found was a

00:40:44.830 --> 00:41:02.126
distribution. He found
a distribution.

00:40:30.000 --> 00:40:54.660
And, if you look more closely at the
distribution, here is what he found.

00:40:54.660 --> 00:40:59.330
He found that some droplets had a
certain velocity,

00:40:59.330 --> 00:41:03.990
and then others had a velocity plus
some step. And he couldn't get

00:41:03.990 --> 00:41:08.660
values of velocity in between
certain steps.

00:41:08.660 --> 00:41:13.330
He reasoned then that the charge,
since he could vary voltage

00:41:13.330 --> 00:41:17.990
continuously but got a discontinuous
variation in velocity,

00:41:17.990 --> 00:41:22.660
his conclusion was that the charge
must be discontinuously attached

00:41:22.660 --> 00:41:28.120
to the droplet.
Out of that he concludes charge must

00:41:28.120 --> 00:41:34.370
be quantized. Charge is quantized.
In other words, it comes in batches

00:41:34.370 --> 00:41:40.620
of a certain unit.
Charge is quantized.

00:41:40.620 --> 00:41:46.870
And, secondly, he was able to
measure the value of the

00:41:46.870 --> 00:41:52.260
elemental charge.
We use the term element to mean the

00:41:52.260 --> 00:41:56.790
lowest value. The element is carbon.
That is the smallest unit.

00:41:56.790 --> 00:42:01.330
Chemically this is the smallest
unit of charge.

00:42:01.330 --> 00:42:05.860
And he gave us a value that turns
out to be 1.6 times 10 to the minus

00:42:05.860 --> 00:42:10.390
19 coulombs in modern times.
And the electron has a negative

00:42:10.390 --> 00:42:14.930
charge, so we would say the charge
on the electron is minus 1.

00:42:14.930 --> 00:42:19.460
. But I want you to learn this as e
being the elementary charge.

00:42:19.460 --> 00:42:38.586
E is the finest charge that is
available to be attached.

00:42:04.000 --> 00:42:30.600
And so now if we take the value of
the Faraday, Faraday found that to

00:42:30.600 --> 00:42:37.200
get 107 grams of silver required 96,
85 coulombs. This is on the basis

00:42:37.200 --> 00:42:43.800
of the integral of the current times
the time. And Millikan said that e

00:42:43.800 --> 00:42:50.400
is equal to 1.
times 10 to the minus 19 coulombs.

00:42:50.400 --> 00:43:07.600
This is coulombs per charge and
this is coulombs per mole.

00:42:37.000 --> 00:43:02.330
If you divide the two of them
through you will get 6.

00:43:02.330 --> 00:43:07.660
2 times 10 to the plus 23 per mole.
So this is how much charge there is

00:43:07.660 --> 00:43:12.990
in a mole of electrons.
This is the number of carbons there

00:43:12.990 --> 00:43:18.330
is in a mole of carbon.
And this is given the value the

00:43:18.330 --> 00:43:23.410
notation N Avogadro **NAv**.
Avogadro's number we call it.

00:43:23.410 --> 00:43:28.240
Avogadro was a professor of
chemistry at the University of Turin

00:43:28.240 --> 00:43:33.080
who did a lot of work on gas laws,
understanding the number of gas

00:43:33.080 --> 00:43:37.910
particles in a given volume at a
given temperature.

00:43:37.910 --> 00:43:42.740
Isn't this nice? They name
constants after professors.

00:43:42.740 --> 00:43:47.580
They didn't name it after a
baseball player. They named

00:43:47.580 --> 00:43:52.830
it after a professor.
So now we know the Avogadro number

00:43:52.830 --> 00:43:58.490
and are able to count the quantities
accordingly. What I am going to do

00:43:58.490 --> 00:44:04.160
next day is go into the larger
stoichiometry and understand the

00:44:04.160 --> 00:44:09.830
principles of mass balance and
reactivity. But before you go,

00:44:09.830 --> 00:44:15.490
hold it, I don't want you racing off.
We should be going to 55 minutes

