00:45:04.930 --> 00:45:09.190
but I think this will go through
fairly quickly.

00:45:09.190 --> 00:45:13.460
Maybe not. It has no protons,
so therefore, it has no electrons.

00:45:13.460 --> 00:45:17.730
Because proton number equals
electron number,

00:45:17.730 --> 00:45:37.326
which means if it has no protons its
atomic number is zero.

00:45:02.000 --> 00:45:27.090
So you are learning already.
However, it does have one neutron.

00:45:27.090 --> 00:45:32.180
It has 125 assistants to the
neutron, it has 75 vice neutrons and

00:45:32.180 --> 00:45:37.270
111 assistants to the vice neutrons.
That gives it a mass number of 312.

00:45:37.270 --> 00:45:42.360
The 312 particles are held together
in a nucleus by a force that

00:45:42.360 --> 00:45:47.450
involves the continuous exchange of
meson-like particles

00:45:47.450 --> 00:45:52.250
called memo-ons.
These memo-ons just go back and

00:45:52.250 --> 00:45:56.750
forth. Now, there are no electrons
so there can be no electronic mail.

00:45:56.750 --> 00:46:01.250
We speculate there may be neutronic
mail here. But,

00:46:01.250 --> 00:46:05.750
anyway, let's talk about the
properties. Since it has no

00:46:05.750 --> 00:46:10.250
electrons, it must be chemically
inert. However,

00:46:10.250 --> 00:46:14.750
it can be detected indirectly
because it seems to impede every

00:46:14.750 --> 00:46:19.350
reaction in which it is present.
According to the discovers,

00:46:19.350 --> 00:46:24.070
the presence of a few nanograms of
administratium made one reaction

00:46:24.070 --> 00:46:28.780
that normally takes less than a
